Your website is often the first impression a potential customer gets of your business. If that impression is "this place looks outdated" or "I can't figure out how to contact them," you're losing money.

Here are five signs it's time to invest in a redesign.

## 1. It takes more than 3 seconds to load

Google's own research shows that **53% of mobile users leave a site that takes longer than 3 seconds to load**. That's more than half your visitors — gone before they even see your content.

**Quick test:** Open your site on your phone using mobile data (not WiFi). Count to three. If it's still loading, you have a problem.

**The fix:** A hand-coded site built for speed can load in under 1 second — no unnecessary code, served from 300+ servers worldwide. That's what we did for [Fade House Barbershop](/work/fade-cuts-barbershop) and their mobile-first audience.

## 2. It doesn't look right on phones

Over 60% of web traffic comes from mobile devices. If your site requires pinching, zooming, or horizontal scrolling on a phone, you're telling mobile visitors they don't matter.

**Quick test:** Pull up your site on your phone. Can you read everything without zooming? Can you tap buttons easily? Is the contact form usable?

**The fix:** A mobile-first redesign ensures your site works perfectly on the smallest screens first, then scales up for desktop. Not the other way around.

## 3. You can't update it yourself

If changing your hours or adding a new service requires calling a developer (or worse, you just don't bother), your website is a liability, not an asset.

**The real cost:** Outdated hours, old menus, removed services still listed — these aren't just annoying. They actively drive away customers who feel misled.

**The fix:** A modern CMS (content management system) lets you update text, images, and pages yourself — no code required. Changes go live in seconds.

## 4. It's not showing up on Google

Search "your service + your city" on Google. If you're not on the first page, potential customers are finding your competitors instead.

**Why it matters:** 75% of searchers never scroll past the first page. If you're on page 2, you're effectively invisible.

**The fix:** SEO isn't magic — it's structure. Clean code, fast load times, proper meta tags, structured data, and a complete Google Business Profile are the foundation. Most older websites miss at least three of these.

## 5. You're embarrassed to share it

This is the simplest test. When someone asks for your website, do you hesitate? Do you say "it's not great" before sharing the link? Do you direct people to your Facebook page instead?

Your website should be something you're proud to share — a digital storefront that represents the quality of your actual work.

**The fix:** A custom-built website that matches the quality of your business. Not a template. Not a page builder. Something uniquely yours.

